  "prompt": "Build an asc2 RMSNorm capability for float32 on C310 (Ascend950PR_9599). Use torch.Tensor inputs (numpy is silently zeroed on C310). Provide TWO @asc2.jit kernels mirroring CANN arch35: a full_row kernel (KernelRmsNormRegBase analogue) where num_cols is asc.ConstExpr[int] and the row tile fits in UB, and a split_d kernel (KernelRmsNormRegBaseSplitD analogue) where both num_rows and num_cols are runtime int and the kernel streams along D in tile_cols=64 tiles with host-side zero padding. Both kernels distribute rows via `for row in asc2.range(asc2.block_idx(), num_rows, asc2.block_num())`. Use asc2.reduce_sum for sum_sq accumulation. Seed sum_sq in split_d with a PlainValue zero: `sum_sq = asc2.reduce_sum(asc2.full([1, tile_cols], 0.0, dtype=asc.float32))`. Provide a host-side dispatcher rms_norm_launch(x, gamma, eps) that picks full_row when num_cols * dtype_bytes <= 64KB and num_cols % 8 == 0, otherwise split_d. Verify both regimes in one run with atol=1e-4, rtol=1e-4 against a torch reference at shapes (8, 256) and (8, 1055).",
